-- Canaccord Names Feneley Head of Healthcare Banking Team
-- B y   A l b e r t i n a   T o r s o l i
-- 2013-03-19T18:24:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-19/canaccord-names-feneley-head-of-healthcare-banking-team.html
Canaccord Genuity  Ltd. appointed
Julian Feneley head of healthcare investment banking in Europe.  Feneley will be based in London and report to Adrian Haxby,
Canaccord’s head of European investment banking, Canaccord
Genuity said in an e-mailed statement today. Canaccord Genuity
is the investment banking unit of Canaccord Financial Inc.,
based in Vancouver.  His previous positions include serving as head of
 Britesmile Inc. , a seller of a teeth-whitening system. He also
worked as senior member of the  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM)  healthcare
investment-banking team in Europe, advising on transactions such
as the creation of Novartis AG and AstraZeneca Plc.  Feneley “will play a key role in further strengthening our
advisory capabilities in this important sector,” Alexis de Rosnay, chief executive officer of Canaccord Genuity’s U.K. and
European operations, said in today’s statement.  Feneley has been a doctor at Guy’s Hospital in  London ,
graduated from London University, and worked in both Europe and
the U.S., Canaccord Genuity said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Albertina Torsoli in Paris at 
